<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-mKGSGXv8absfI__Gs7vFjA" name="prepare_reuse_assessment,_ocr9oPaBEdqJ3rP9LdCKZw" guid="-mKGSGXv8absfI__Gs7vFjA" changeDate="2007-03-15T12:02:40.156-0700" version="1.0.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The scope of the reuse assessment should be selected first. In general, it is not good practice to apply reuse&#xD;
    principles to the entire enterprise at one time. As input to the reuse assessment, the business problem and priority&#xD;
    need to be understood. This provides the necessary context and scope for focusing the reuse assessment.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Therefore,&amp;nbsp;if the business problem is scoped or can be scoped to a specific organization, team, or project, then&#xD;
    the reuse assessment should be scoped as well. The reuse assessment evaluates two major elements for the selected&#xD;
    scope: 1) reuse capability and 2) reuse opportunity.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Reuse capability describes the organization's ability to conduct reuse activities. Reuse opportunity describes the&#xD;
    extent to which recurring problems and recurring solutions exist within the selected scope.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    An organization's reuse capabilities are increased when the following factors are in place:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Management support&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Mature software process in the organization&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    There are generally more reuse opportunities when the following factors are in place:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Well understood domains&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Architecture to support reuse&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Mature versioning and configuration management&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    When creating the reuse assessment, evaluate each of the factors in the two lists above. Sample questions to consider&#xD;
    on each of these factors are listed below.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Management support&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Will management specify policies and support asset reuse?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Will management provide top-down support for investing with bottom-up implementation?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Mature software process in the organization&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Do the project teams follow a repeatable software process?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Are there management artifacts produced from the process, and does management use them?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Well-understood domains&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Is the business problem space understood by the software organization?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Architecture to support reuse&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Will the software architecture permit assets to be harvested and plugged in for reuse?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Mature versioning and configuration management&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Does the software team practice source code versioning and configuration management?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        What is the release cycle for delivering software in the organization?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="_MTYXcNMpEdu6ttMl0uhyhw" name="Determine Scope of Reuse Assessment" guid="_MTYXcNMpEdu6ttMl0uhyhw">
    <sectionDescription>Describe the scope of the assessment. This&amp;nbsp;may be for the entire enterprise, or for one community, which in turn may&#xD;
be a division or&amp;nbsp;a single&amp;nbsp;project. For the target scope establish approvals and agreements to proceed with&#xD;
assessment.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_O1NbANMpEdu6ttMl0uhyhw" name="Determine Reuse Capability" guid="_O1NbANMpEdu6ttMl0uhyhw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Interview personnel within the reuse scope to determine:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Skill sets&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Previous reuse experiences&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Willingness to participate in reuse efforts:&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li style=&quot;LIST-STYLE-TYPE: none&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Using asset repository&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Developing reusable assets&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Hurdles to block reuse efforts&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Management support&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Maturity of software development process practiced&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Practice of versioning and configuration management&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_Qz3gENMpEdu6ttMl0uhyhw" name="Determine Reuse Opportunity" guid="_Qz3gENMpEdu6ttMl0uhyhw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Interview personnel within reuse scope to determine:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Functional redundancy across projects, communities&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Nature of software architecture&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Non-functional constraints on systems&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Stability of business domain&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_Tky18P8jEduLr5zGs322wA" name="Analyze Findings" guid="_Tky18P8jEduLr5zGs322wA">
    <sectionDescription>Collect the materials from the interviews and evaluate common messages and issues.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_Yv5o4P8jEduLr5zGs322wA" name="Prepare Reuse Assessment Report" guid="_Yv5o4P8jEduLr5zGs322wA">
    <sectionDescription>Use the reuse assessment template to prepare the reuse assessment report.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>Provide input to decision to proceed with asset reuse initiative.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
